# Specification

## EPIC 1 — Annotation Semantic Triples

### 1.1 Semantic Triple Definition

Every annotation in the Standard Annotation Library (§14 of GASD 1.1) SHALL be defined by a **semantic triple**: `(structural_predicate, runtime_contract, environmental_dependency)`.

| Component | Definition | Verification Method |
|---|---|---|
| **Structural Predicate** | A first-order predicate verifiable by static analysis of the AST, CFG, or call graph | Deterministic — pattern matching, control flow analysis |
| **Runtime Behavior Contract** | A universally-quantified property testable by systematic adversarial input generation | Property-based testing (SmallCheck/QuickCheck semantics) |
| **Environmental Dependency** | A conditional proposition whose truth depends on the deployment environment | Explicit assumption statement |

**Formal semantic triples for all Standard Annotations:**

#### Data Validation Annotations

| Annotation | Structural Predicate | Runtime Contract | Environmental Dependency |
|---|---|---|---|
| `@range(min, max)` | Guard clause present: `∀x ∈ dom(f). guard(x) → min ≤ x ≤ max` | Boundary inputs (min-1, min, max, max+1, null) produce correct accept/reject | None |
| `@min_length(n)` | Length guard present: `∀x ∈ dom(f). len(x) ≥ n enforced` | Input of length n-1 rejected, length n accepted | None |
| `@max_length(n)` | Length guard present: `∀x ∈ dom(f). len(x) ≤ n enforced` | Input of length n accepted, length n+1 rejected | None |
| `@format(fmt)` | Regex/validator constant present matching the named format | 10,000+ adversarial inputs per format type all handled correctly | None |
| `@unique(scope)` | Uniqueness check call routed through specified scope | Duplicate input correctly rejected; concurrent duplicates handled | DB-level unique constraint exists and is enforced |
| `@default(val)` | Default value assignment present in constructor/factory | Missing input receives exactly `val` | None |
| `@constraint(desc)` | Validation logic present matching described constraint | Systematic inputs violating the constraint are rejected | None |

#### Architectural Annotations

| Annotation | Structural Predicate | Runtime Contract | Environmental Dependency |
|---|---|---|---|
| `@injectable` | DI-compatible constructor generated (no `new` instantiation) | Component resolved from DI container at runtime | DI container configured correctly |
| `@mockable` | Interface abstraction generated; no concrete class dependency | Mock implementation substitutable in tests | None |
| `@transaction_type(ACID)` | `@Transactional` annotation present, scope correct | Forced rollback scenarios roll back all writes within scope | DB isolation ≥ READ COMMITTED; connection pool configured; no cross-service TX propagation |
| `@transaction_type(SAGA)` | Saga orchestrator/choreography pattern present | Compensation logic executes on partial failure | All saga participants implement compensating transactions |

#### Implementation Modifier Annotations

| Annotation | Structural Predicate | Runtime Contract | Environmental Dependency |
|---|---|---|---|
| `@async` | Return type is Future/Promise/Void; non-blocking dispatch | Async operation does not block synchronous caller; completes eventually | Thread pool size ≥ required concurrency |
| `@retry(n)` | Retry wrapper present in code with count = n | Under injected failures 1..n: retries occur; failure n+1: exception propagates | Operations are idempotent OR compensation logic present |
| `@timeout(ms)` | Timeout parameter present in client/call configuration | Under induced latency > ms: TimeoutException thrown within tolerance | External service latency distribution within configured bounds |
| `@external` | Network boundary error handling present (try/catch or equivalent) | Connection failure, timeout, and malformed response all handled | External service reachable at configured endpoint |
| `@hash(algo)` | Named algorithm implementation present; no alternative hash functions reachable in call graph | Hash output matches expected format for named algorithm | Algorithm library available in runtime classpath |
| `@circuit_breaker` | Circuit breaker wrapper present with open/half-open/closed states | After N consecutive failures, circuit opens; after timeout, half-open test | None |
| `@cacheable(ttl)` | Cache annotation present with correct TTL value | Cache hit returns consistent value within TTL window; expiry triggers refresh | Cache infrastructure available; eviction policy compatible |
| `@idempotent` | No side-effect duplication on repeated calls with same input | Repeated identical calls produce identical system state | None |

#### Extended Annotations

| Annotation | Structural Predicate | Runtime Contract | Environmental Dependency |
|---|---|---|---|
| `@sensitive` | Field masked in all log output; encryption at rest applied | Sensitive value never appears in plaintext logs under any code path | Encryption key management configured |
| `@authorized(role)` | Role check present before protected operation | Unauthorized role correctly rejected; authorized role correctly admitted | Authentication/authorization service available |

### 1.2 Semantic Registry

A centralized **Annotation Semantic Registry** SHALL store all semantic triples.

**Format:**

```gasd
// Registry entry (internal representation)
ANNOTATION_SEMANTIC @retry(n):
    STRUCTURAL:
        "Retry wrapper present in code with count = n"
        VERIFICATION: AST_PATTERN_MATCH
    RUNTIME:
        "Under injected failures 1..n: retries; failure n+1: throws"
        VERIFICATION: PROPERTY_BASED_TEST
    ENVIRONMENTAL:
        "Operations are idempotent OR compensation logic present"
        VERIFICATION: ASSUMPTION_STATEMENT
```

**Rules:**
- Registry MUST support lookup by annotation type
- Registry MUST support versioning (semantic definitions may evolve across GASD versions)
- Resolution MUST be deterministic — same annotation always resolves to same triple
- Registry MUST be accessible to all processing modules (parsers, analyzers, linters)

